---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Behnaz" description="A bit about me, my path, and what I'm working on.">
  <section class="rise">
    <p class="mb-3 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-coral)]">about</p>
    <h1 class="mb-8">a little intro 🌷</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Behnaz</strong>, a data scientist and researcher
        with a background in <em>photonics, mechanical engineering, and a
        stubborn love of asking why</em>. I grew up in Mashhad, did my bachelor's
        in mechanical engineering, and then moved to Germany for a master's in
        Lasers and Photonics at Ruhr University Bochum.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days I work at the <a href="https://www.medit.hia.rwth-aachen.de/">
        Chair of Medical Information Technology (MedIT)</a> at RWTH Aachen,
        where I build deep-learning models that read body temperature from
        thermal infrared images — somewhere at the intersection of optics,
        machine learning, and bedside medicine.
      </p>
      <h2>what i think about</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>turning messy experimental data into something you can actually trust</li>
        <li>where photonics meets ML — spectroscopy, thermal imaging, computational optics</li>
        <li>how to teach things clearly, especially the things i had to learn the hard way</li>
        <li>good bread, good tea, and the slow rituals around them</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>elsewhere</h2>
      <p>
        I read in three languages, write in two, and pretend to dream in
        German. Beyond the lab, I bake, sketch, take terrible film photos
        of nice clouds, and run on the Aachener Wald trails when the weather
        agrees.
      </p>
      <p>
        The best way to reach me is by
        <a href="mailto:hello@behnaz.example">email</a>. I usually reply
        within a day or two — unless there's a really good loaf of sourdough
        in the oven.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
